cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with independent sets in graphs and their reconfiguration. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for solving the problem. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as cographs are a class of graphs that have applications in computational geometry. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the concept of reconfiguration graphs has applications in game theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper deals with the complexity of deciding whether a reconfiguration graph is connected.
